The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has suspended, indefinitely, all recruitment processes into the Service due to concerns about the hike of coronavirus cases in the country. This was disclosed yesterday in a statement signed by the media assistant to the Commandant General, Ekunola Gbenga, exclusively obtained by LEADERSHIP. The Corps announced in the statement that the periods for shortlisting of applications are postponed and information relative to the new dates will be given later, but added that list of applications so far shortlisted remains intact. The NSCDC recruitment process was to allow the Corps to recruit 10,000 men and officers in to help fight insecurity in the country. While stressing that the wellbeing of prospective applicants and that of the nation remains their priority, the NSCDC said, “We are monitoring the ongoing Coronavirus (COVID-19) situation and are continuing to follow the latest government guidelines. DETAILS LATER…..